{"name": "dtw", "metadata": {"name": "dtw", "version": "1.4.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering"], "home_page": "https://github.com/pierre-rouanet/dtw", "license": "GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Python DTW Module", "upload_time": 1572337200}, "documentation": ["\nDtw is a Python Module for computing Dynamic Time Warping distance. It can be used as a similarity measured between temporal sequences.\n\nMore info can be found at: https://github.com/pierre-rouanet/dtw\n\nIt is compatible with Python 2.7-3.6 and is distributed under the GPLv3 license.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test.Test", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test.Test.test_distance", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test.Test.test_symmetry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test.Test.test_warping", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test.Test.test_input_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_import", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_import.ImportTestCase", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_import.ImportTestCase.test_import", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_import.ImportTestCase.test_has_version", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_fastvsnormal", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_fastvsnormal.FastVsNormalTestCase", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_fastvsnormal.FastVsNormalTestCase.test_fast_vs_normal_1D", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_fastvsnormal.FastVsNormalTestCase.test_fast_vs_normal_ND", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_fastvsnormal.FastVsNormalTestCase.test_specific_case", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dtw", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "dtw.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "dtw.version.version", "project": null}}, {"name": "dtw.accelerated_dtw", "xref": {"fqname": "dtw.dtw.accelerated_dtw", "project": null}}, {"name": "dtw.dtw", "xref": {"fqname": "dtw.dtw.dtw", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "dtw.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dtw.version.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dtw.dtw.dtw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dist", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "warp", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "w", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "s", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Computes Dynamic Time Warping (DTW) of two sequences.\n\n:param array x: N1*M array\n:param array y: N2*M array\n:param func dist: distance used as cost measure\n:param int warp: how many shifts are computed.\n:param int w: window size limiting the maximal distance between indices of matched entries |i,j|.\n:param float s: weight applied on off-diagonal moves of the path. As s gets larger, the warping path is increasingly biased towards the diagonal\nReturns the minimum distance, the cost matrix, the accumulated cost matrix, and the wrap path."]}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.accelerated_dtw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dist", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "warp", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Computes Dynamic Time Warping (DTW) of two sequences in a faster way.\nInstead of iterating through each element and calculating each distance,\nthis uses the cdist function from scipy (https://docs.scipy.org/doc/scipy/reference/generated/scipy.spatial.distance.cdist.html)\n\n:param array x: N1*M array\n:param array y: N2*M array\n:param string or func dist: distance parameter for cdist. When string is given, cdist uses optimized functions for the distance metrics.\nIf a string is passed, the distance function can be 'braycurtis', 'canberra', 'chebyshev', 'cityblock', 'correlation', 'cosine', 'dice', 'euclidean', 'hamming', 'jaccard', 'kulsinski', 'mahalanobis', 'matching', 'minkowski', 'rogerstanimoto', 'russellrao', 'seuclidean', 'sokalmichener', 'sokalsneath', 'sqeuclidean', 'wminkowski', 'yule'.\n:param int warp: how many shifts are computed.\nReturns the minimum distance, the cost matrix, the accumulated cost matrix, and the wrap path."]}, {"name": "dtw.dtw._traceback", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "D", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "dtw.dtw.w", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.s", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.x", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.y", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.dist_fun", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.w", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.x", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.y", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.dist_fun", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.x", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.y", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dtw.dtw.dist_fun", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}